          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The yield, Y(A,q,Ek), corresponding to a particular",
                "mass number A, ionic charge q, and kinetic energy Ek,",
                "is extracted from the two-dimensional plot of dE vs E.",
                "Two approaches were used:",
                "- experiments 1 and 2 :",
                " kinetic energy distribution was assumed to be",
                "independent from ionic charge distribution;",
                " q distribution was obtained at optimal Ek using",
                "formula (1);",
                " Y(a) was obtained by formula (2);",
                " Gaussians fits to the data were applied;",
                "- experiment 3 :",
                "  pure statistical analysis (instead of Gaussian fits);",
                "  the correlation between kinetic energy distributions",
                "  and ionic charge distributions is deduced from the",
                "  data and taken into account in the uncertainty",
                "  analysis;",
                "  typically from 2 up to 4 scans across ionic charge",
                "  at different Ek were performed and from 2 up to 4",
                "  mass measurements have been obtained and compared in",
                "  order to deduce a mean value per mass with a reduced",
                "  uncertainty.",
                "Burn-up was taken into account using results of",
                "measurement of the mass 136 yield, carried out",
                "periodically (~ every 8hr), resulting in burn-up curve."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Contributions from other Pu isotopes were negligible."
              ]
            }
          ],
